Method Detail

getStreams

java.util.List<Stream> getStreams()
A list of Stream objects to which this event pertains.

This is usually an array containing only one Stream object, corresponding to the stream that was added (in the case of a onStreamCreated() or deleted (in the case of a onStreamDestroyed() However, the array may contain multiple Stream objects if multiple streams were added or deleted.

getSource

java.lang.Object getSource()
Used to identify the session the event belongs to.

Returns:
Returns the session object that the event belongs to.
